Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.47,0:00:03.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,欢迎回来。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.07,0:00:04.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在本次讲座中，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.01,0:00:08.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们将学习如何在 CSS 中使用颜色。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.30,0:00:12.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而，在我们真正回到我们的 CSS 之前，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.55,0:00:15.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们首先需要了解一点理论
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.75,0:00:18.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如何使用代码表示颜色。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.97,0:00:24.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在，有很多表示颜色的方法
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.02,0:00:28.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在计算机中，基本上是在编写代码中，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.10,0:00:32.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但更传统的模型之一是 RGB 模型。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.83,0:00:34.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以在 RGB 模型中，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.79,0:00:37.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每一种颜色都可以表示
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.51,0:00:42.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,通过红色、绿色和蓝色的任意组合。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.03,0:00:45.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以看起来像这样。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.95,0:00:49.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也许你已经看过这样的图表
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.06,0:00:51.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在学校的某个地方或类似的地方。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.63,0:00:57.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以无论如何，为了真正代表某种颜色，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.83,0:01:00.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们需要给出三种基本颜色中的每一种，
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.90,0:01:05.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,0 到 255 之间的任何值。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.16,0:01:06.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就这样，
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.54,0:01:11.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们总共可以定义 1680 万种不同的颜色。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.22,0:01:16.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以让我们用这里的图表稍微理解一下
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.46,0:01:19.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从纯红色开始。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.35,0:01:24.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当然，在这个通道中，红色是最大的，
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.22,0:01:28.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是255和其他两个通道。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.32,0:01:31.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以其他两种基色为零。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.97,0:01:36.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以没有任何绿色，也没有任何蓝色。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.71,0:01:39.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这就是为什么它是纯红色的。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.51,0:01:40.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,再说一次，
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.39,0:01:42.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,红色通道处于最大值
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.93,0:01:45.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而所有其他的都为零。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.60,0:01:49.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当然，蓝色和绿色也是如此。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.26,0:01:54.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以在蓝色中，蓝色通道最大为 255，
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.10,0:01:57.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,另一个是零并且是绿色的，
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.32,0:02:00.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,绿色的情况基本相同。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.29,0:02:02.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,接下来我们有白色。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.60,0:02:05.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在白色中，我们拥有所有三种颜色
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.52,0:02:08.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最大为 255。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.83,0:02:12.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以基本上所有颜色都最多
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.39,0:02:15.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在另一端给我们一个完整的白色
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.89,0:02:19.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,光谱中，当我们所有的颜色都为零时，
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.70,0:02:22.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们得到一个完整的黑色。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.64,0:02:26.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最后，我们这里的其他三种颜色
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.20,0:02:30.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是其他两种颜色的混合，它们是由它们制成的。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.33,0:02:34.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以你会看到这里的洋红色是红色和蓝色的
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.04,0:02:37.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最大，根本没有绿色。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.37,0:02:42.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后我们有这个我认为被称为青色或青色的颜色，
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.41,0:02:47.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它在零处有红色，在最大值处有 GNB。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.40,0:02:50.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最后黄色的蓝色为零
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.45,0:02:53.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,另外两个是255。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.02,0:02:54.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,伟大的。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.88,0:02:57.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以我希望这是有道理的。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.71,0:03:00.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在我们有了基本的了解
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.62,0:03:03.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,RGB 模型的工作原理，
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.04,0:03:06.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,让我们实际看看我们如何代表
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.16,0:03:09.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或者我们如何在 CSS 中定义颜色。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.53,0:03:14.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以在 CSS 中，我们有两种写颜色的方法
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.38,0:03:16.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,使用 RGB 模型。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.30,0:03:21.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些是 RGB 表示法和十六进制表示法。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.41,0:03:24.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此，通过使用 RGB 表示法，
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.22,0:03:28.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们所做的就是在 CSS 中使用这个 RGB 函数，
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.49,0:03:31.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后我们简单地为每个指定值
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.76,0:03:35.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,三个颜色通道，红色，绿色和蓝色。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.66,0:03:37.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,例如，
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.06,0:03:40.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果我们将绿色和蓝色设置为最大值，
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.54,0:03:44.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后我们得到这个青色，就像我们看到的一样
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.68,0:03:46.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在最后一张幻灯片中。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.57,0:03:50.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,另一个例子，这是一个更真实的世界，\N00:03:50,120--> 00:03:52,920\N这是橙色吗？\N\N69
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.92,0:03:55.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以这里是每个频道的数字
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.08,0:03:57.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,看起来更随意一点。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.47,0:04:00.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以这就是我们如何获得真实的颜色
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.81,0:04:04.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,使用 CSS 并使用 RGB 表示法。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.81,0:04:07.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那么除了正常的RGB功能外，
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.96,0:04:11.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还有具有透明度的RGB。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.82,0:04:14.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,透明度也称为alpha。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.89,0:04:18.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这就是为什么这个函数被称为 RGBA。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.66,0:04:22.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以在这里我们可以指定第四个值，
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.05,0:04:24.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这种情况下是 0.3，
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.05,0:04:28.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后这将使这种颜色具有透明度
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.35,0:04:29.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,正如我们在这里看到的。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.75,0:04:34.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,看看这个另一个例子，如果我们，例如定义
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.93,0:04:36.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,alpha 值为 0.7，
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.48,0:04:40.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后我们看到这个颜色实际上是透明的
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.93,0:04:44.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当我们把它放在另一种颜色上时可见
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.66,0:04:47.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像这个绿色广场。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.12,0:04:50.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在，当然我们不必手动上来
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.11,0:04:52.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些颜色的这些数字。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.61,0:04:53.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好的。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.66,0:04:57.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以我们不必像手动写244、179、63
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.80,0:05:02.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为了得到这个橙子。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.00,0:05:06.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以通常我们只是从某个地方复制某种颜色，
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.32,0:05:10.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或者我们也可以在 VS 代码中使用颜色选择器生成它。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.96,0:05:14.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这样就会自动给我们这些数字。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.51,0:05:17.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但这一切仍然非常重要，让你知道
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.64,0:05:20.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些数字实际上意味着什么。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.30,0:05:22.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好的。但继续前进，
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.17,0:05:25.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在让我们谈谈十六进制表示法，
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.48,0:05:29.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这实际上在 CSS 中使用得更多。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.03,0:05:31.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以这里用十六进制表示法，
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.80,0:05:36.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们不使用从零到 255 的刻度，
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.25,0:05:40.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但我们使用从零到 FF 的比例。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.76,0:05:45.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而且FF基本和255一样，
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.40,0:05:48.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但以十六进制表示。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.20,0:05:51.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们不需要深入研究这实际上意味着什么，
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.90,0:05:54.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但基本上是十六进制数
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.08,0:05:58.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不要从零到九，而是从零到十五。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.83,0:06:02.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以有 16 个不同的数字，而不仅仅是 10 个，
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.54,0:06:05.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最后一个 F。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.08,0:06:10.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这就是为什么这里的 FF 意味着 255。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.54,0:06:13.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在把它翻译成 CSS，
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.27,0:06:16.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们像这样写十六进制表示法，
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.26,0:06:20.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,使用哈希值，然后是红色、绿色和蓝色的值，
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.73,0:06:23.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像我在这个屏幕上看到的一样。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.20,0:06:25.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以这当然给了我们
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.28,0:06:29.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,与 RGB 符号完全相同的数字。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.28,0:06:30.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当然也可以这样做
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.96,0:06:35.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,使用我在这里的橙色示例颜色。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.23,0:06:37.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以我们可以表示为使用 F4B33F。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.11,0:06:43.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,再一次，这看起来有点随机
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.07,0:06:46.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以我们通常只是从颜色选择器中复制我们
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.32,0:06:47.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在 VS 代码中。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.94,0:06:50.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在以十六进制表示，
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.03,0:06:52.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还有一种叫做速记的东西，
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.94,0:06:57.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当所有颜色都是相同的对时，我们可以使用它。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.59,0:07:02.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以在我们的青色中，我们有两个零，两个 F，
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.10,0:07:03.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,再一次，两个F。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.69,0:07:07.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以我们可以把债务缩写成我们的速记
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.08,0:07:07.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,写 0FF。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.47,0:07:10.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好的。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.82,0:07:14.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在谈谈我们实际上是如何做事的
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.01,0:07:17.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在现实世界的实践中。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.07,0:07:21.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以在实践中，我们大多使用十六进制表示法，
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.78,0:07:26.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后如果我们需要透明度，我们使用 RGBA 函数。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.19,0:07:30.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此，正如您在左侧看到的 alpha 值。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.83,0:07:34.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最后，关于恩典，
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.59,0:07:36.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是一种特殊的颜色
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.73,0:07:39.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们在 CSS 中一直需要。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.49,0:07:42.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以基本上在RGB模型中，
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.25,0:07:44.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当三个通道中的三种颜色
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.93,0:07:49.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,完全一样，我们得到的是灰色。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.51,0:07:52.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以在光谱的两个极端，
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.78,0:07:56.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当所有值都为零时，我们得到完全黑色，
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.73,0:08:01.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当它们都处于最大值时，所以在 205 处，
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.79,0:08:05.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或在FF，然后我们得到白色。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.58,0:08:07.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但当然还有很多其他的灰色
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.94,0:08:10.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这之间我们可以使用。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.48,0:08:11.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,准确地说，
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.63,0:08:16.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,正好有 256 种纯灰色可供选择。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.09,0:08:20.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,例如，其中之一就是这个。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.60,0:08:25.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以红色、绿色和蓝色都是 69。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.15,0:08:28.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以这给了我们这种漂亮的灰色，
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.18,0:08:33.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它的十六进制代码为 444444
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.14,0:08:38.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在简写符号中可以写成 444。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.73,0:08:42.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以这个，我喜欢用很多的文字颜色。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.33,0:08:45.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当然，让我们看另一个例子。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.24,0:08:49.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而这个所有值都为 183 的，
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.12,0:08:53.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它可以表示为B7B7B7。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.35,0:08:55.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以用十六进制表示
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.81,0:08:59.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你会再次看到这里的三对
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.31,0:09:01.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,完全一样。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.00,0:09:04.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这就是我们实际上拥有的死信号，
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.26,0:09:05.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,灰色。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.21,0:09:07.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好的。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.04,0:09:10.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以现在我们对颜色理论有了一点了解
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.05,0:09:13.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在代码中，尤其是在 CSS 代码中，
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.94,0:09:17.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在让我们快速学习几个 CSS 属性
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.28,0:09:20.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们可以在实践中实际使用颜色。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.81,0:09:26.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,以及最简单的需要颜色值的 CSS 属性
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.36,0:09:28.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只是颜色属性，
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.56,0:09:30.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们之前实际上已经使用过。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.94,0:09:36.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以假设我们希望这里的 H1 有
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.17,0:09:37.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不同的颜色。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.00,0:09:41.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以让我们说颜色，
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.98,0:09:46.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后我将在这里指定一些蓝色。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.22,0:09:48.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,1098 和广告。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.58,0:09:53.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以这给了我们这种漂亮的蓝色。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.32,0:09:55.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以正如我们刚刚学到的，
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.81,0:10:00.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们在红色通道中有 10 个或 1 个零，
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.57,0:10:05.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,绿色通道为 98，蓝色通道为广告。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.97,0:10:08.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在，正如我之前提到的，
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.52,0:10:11.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们通常使用 VS 代码颜色选择器。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.66,0:10:14.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以我们只需将鼠标悬停在一种颜色上即可，
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.90,0:10:18.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后从这里，我们可以选择任何颜色
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.17,0:10:19.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们想要的。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.40,0:10:21.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对？
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.87,0:10:24.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以我们可以把这里的颜色改成别的。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.80,0:10:27.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以这个灰色阴影，然后在那里，
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.95,0:10:31.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们基本上可以定义灰色应该有多深。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.07,0:10:35.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,此外，如果我们点击顶部的此处，
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.15,0:10:38.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以在这里的这个值，这将改变符号。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.34,0:10:41.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以现在我们有了这个 HSL，
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.47,0:10:43.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们实际上并没有谈论，
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.74,0:10:47.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是如果我们再次点击，我们得到了 RGB。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.18,0:10:50.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以这和以前的颜色完全一样，
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.40,0:10:52.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但使用RGB功能。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.40,0:10:54.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对？
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.67,0:10:56.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以让我保存它。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.12,0:10:58.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在你会看到我们有这个绿色。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.41,0:11:04.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此，如果我们再次将其悬停，我们将返回颜色选择器。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.34,0:11:06.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在这个实际上是滑块
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.68,0:11:08.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为 alpha 值。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.70,0:11:10.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以如果我们开始把它往下拉，
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.78,0:11:15.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后您会看到它自动更改为RGBA。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.70,0:11:16.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好的？
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.53,0:11:20.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后我们可以在这里定义 alpha 值。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.48,0:11:23.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以它实际上已经被保存了，
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.84,0:11:27.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你看到现在颜色有点透明了。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.43,0:11:29.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对？
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.29,0:11:33.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果我们把它甚至接近于零，
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.37,0:11:36.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后现在它几乎完全消失了。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.72,0:11:40.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好的。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.05,0:11:43.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这就是我们使用颜色选择器的方式，
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.02,0:11:46.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但现在让我们回到我们原来的颜色。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.95,0:11:47.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以1098ad。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.29,0:11:52.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好的。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.79,0:11:55.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,实际上，我想向您展示另一个不错的技巧，
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.85,0:11:59.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以如果你只想要颜色选择器，
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.04,0:12:04.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,您可以先指定任何颜色，例如白色，
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.11,0:12:07.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,通过使用 FFF，然后您只需将颜色悬停
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.16,0:12:09.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后你进入颜色选择器。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.73,0:12:12.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好的。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.56,0:12:15.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以如果你想要它，例如，这个粉红色，
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.43,0:12:19.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你可以在这里选择，也许有一些阿尔法
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.76,0:12:21.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你去吧。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.23,0:12:24.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在它应用了这种粉红色，
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.05,0:12:27.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为当我们有两个相同的定义时，
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.35,0:12:28.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它只会使用最后一个。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.82,0:12:32.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是，稍后再谈。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.00,0:12:35.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以让我们摆脱它。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.21,0:12:39.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在我们实际上也想要 h2 和 h3
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.28,0:12:40.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,具有完全相同的颜色。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.03,0:12:43.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以这个和这个。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.96,0:12:47.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那么我们应该怎么做呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.10,0:12:50.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们是否应该在这里简单地复制这个属性
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.77,0:12:54.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,到这个声明，然后在这里和这里粘贴它？
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.63,0:12:57.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好吧，不是真的，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.59,0:13:00.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为那样我们就会有完全相同的代码
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.11,0:13:01.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在多个地方。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.61,0:13:05.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这绝不是一个好主意，因为想象一下，
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.00,0:13:09.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后我们想更改颜色，例如更改为橙色。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.03,0:13:10.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后我们将不得不通过
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.87,0:13:14.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所有三种颜色定义并在那里更改它们。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.90,0:13:16.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以一一改变。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.96,0:13:20.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当然，这不是我们想要的。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.07,0:13:24.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此，我们可以定义一个选择器列表，
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.53,0:13:26.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像我们在这里做的一样。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.54,0:13:29.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但现在只有我们想要的
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.60,0:13:31.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,蓝领申请。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.09,0:13:35.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以这是h1，h2，h3
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.16,0:13:41.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在让我们简单地抓取它并粘贴到这里，
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.04,0:13:44.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,给它一个保险箱，然后就可以了。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.26,0:13:50.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以现在 h1、h2 和 h3 具有这种蓝色。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.15,0:13:55.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而现在，正如你可能已经注意到的那样，
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.55,0:14:00.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们现在还有另一个应用于 h1 的选择器。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.79,0:14:04.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以我们有这个，这个和这个，
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.19,0:14:07.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,事实上，他们所有的风格
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.75,0:14:10.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在正在应用于此元素。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.45,0:14:15.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,接下来，让我们也为文本的其余部分定义一种颜色。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.29,0:14:19.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以现在剩下的文字完全是黑色的，
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.15,0:14:22.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是让我们用我给你看的那个灰色
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.66,0:14:23.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在其中一张幻灯片中。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.81,0:14:27.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,实际上，让我们在这里这样做。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.17,0:14:31.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以我们希望这篇文章基本上适用于一切，
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.90,0:14:36.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,即使这些在这里，颜色也会被覆盖
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.67,0:14:38.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,之后。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.26,0:14:40.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,再一次，我们将了解为什么
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.21,0:14:42.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,以及如何在单独的讲座中进行。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.97,0:14:45.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以记住灰色，
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.88,0:14:49.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它需要在所有三个通道中具有相同的值。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.10,0:14:54.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,比如说 444444，像这样，
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.23,0:14:56.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果你记得速记，
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.61,0:14:58.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那么我们可以进一步缩写它。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.89,0:15:02.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为每一对都是相同的值
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.21,0:15:04.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一如既往只有44岁，
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.51,0:15:07.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以我们可以像这样让它更短。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.95,0:15:10.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,给它一个保险箱，
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.27,0:15:15.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在确实，这里所有的文字都是灰色的，
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.72,0:15:18.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,除了h1，二和三，
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.11,0:15:20.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,稍后在这里被覆盖。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.40,0:15:22.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,伟大的。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.32,0:15:25.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以现在让我们谈谈另一个 CSS 属性
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.44,0:15:27.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可以接受颜色值，
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.92,0:15:30.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这就是背景颜色属性。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.72,0:15:33.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以现在让我们给出我们的主页标题
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.01,0:15:37.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,略带灰色的背景颜色以使其有点区分
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.13,0:15:39.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从其余的内容。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.45,0:15:42.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那么我们怎么能这样做呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.83,0:15:45.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,让我们一路下来。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.14,0:15:47.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而首先想到的
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.16,0:15:52.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是简单地选择这样的标题，对吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.08,0:15:56.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以这里有一个叫做背景颜色的新属性。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.05,0:16:03.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这里让我们使用另一种漂亮的灰色，
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.61,0:16:04.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是F7F7F7。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.68,0:16:11.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以再一次，你可以看到三种颜色中的颜色，
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.36,0:16:16.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以三个主要的RGB通道是完全一样的。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.08,0:16:19.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,顺便说一句，在颜色选择器中，
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.14,0:16:23.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,无论你在这个颜色滑块中是什么颜色
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.62,0:16:27.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,左边总是有这种灰色阴影。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.52,0:16:29.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以如果你从顶部开始，
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.49,0:16:32.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,您会看到我在这张幻灯片中向您展示的白色。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.26,0:16:36.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在最顶端，你会变成黑色。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.09,0:16:36.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好的？
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.95,0:16:39.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以你总是可以得到灰色
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.36,0:16:42.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果您将滑块移动到非常极端的位置
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.96,0:16:45.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里的左边。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.35,0:16:48.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是现在让我们转到F7F7，它是一种颜色，
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.95,0:16:52.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这很容易记住并且很好用。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.40,0:16:56.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如此微妙的灰色，也许你甚至看不到这里，
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.83,0:16:59.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但希望你能在屏幕上看到它。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.36,0:17:01.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在，这里的问题不仅是，
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.36,0:17:04.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们的页眉是灰色的，
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.07,0:17:05.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还有这个其他标题。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.67,0:17:09.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以也许你可以看到它的到来。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.54,0:17:13.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以解决这个问题的方法是给这个标题一个名字
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.80,0:17:16.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后仅设置此标题的样式。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.51,0:17:19.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在只有这个我们想要设置样式的标题，
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.90,0:17:22.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以我们可以在这里使用一个ID，
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.69,0:17:25.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但考虑到我在上一节课中的解释，
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.31,0:17:28.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们不要那样做，那只是使用一个类。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.76,0:17:32.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们称之为主标题。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.86,0:17:35.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,让我复制一下
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.49,0:17:42.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并将此标头替换为主标头类。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.06,0:17:46.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,事实上，现在只有这里的这个人得到了这种灰色。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.67,0:17:48.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,让我们摆脱这个测试。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.23,0:17:51.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在我们开始。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.58,0:17:53.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好的。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.41,0:17:55.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果你真的看不到这个背景颜色，
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.35,0:17:58.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后只需使用您的颜色选择器
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.27,0:18:01.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只是使用其他一些灰色阴影。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.32,0:18:02.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好的。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.27,0:18:05.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个视频已经播放了很长时间，
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.30,0:18:08.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但我们还是在这里谈谈另一个属性，
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.61,0:18:10.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是关于边界的。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.89,0:18:15.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以我接下来要做的是添加一些边框
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.01,0:18:18.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,到这里的这些相关帖子。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.37,0:18:22.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以基本上让它们现在看起来像这样。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.55,0:18:24.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好的？
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.38,0:18:27.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以我们在底部和顶部，
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.26,0:18:28.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个蓝色边框。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.65,0:18:32.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以这根本不难做到。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.37,0:18:34.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以让我们看看这里的元素是什么。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.94,0:18:37.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就是这张幻灯片。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.35,0:18:40.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以让我们在这里选择它
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.64,0:18:45.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,使用这个元素选择器。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.94,0:18:50.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以元素选择器基本上就是当我们简单的使用名字的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.25,0:18:52.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,的元素来选择它。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.64,0:18:53.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好的？
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.48,0:18:56.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以今年是带点的类选择器。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.39,0:18:58.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是带有哈希的 ID 选择器。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.92,0:19:01.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而当我们简单地使用元素的名称时，
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.33,0:19:04.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们称之为元素选择器。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.17,0:19:06.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在让我们开始实际上给它相同的
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.93,0:19:08.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,背景颜色。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.51,0:19:11.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以背景颜色
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.17,0:19:14.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后我们使用之前使用的那个。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.27,0:19:16.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,VS 代码在这里其实很有帮助
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.72,0:19:20.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为它会扫描 CSS 文档中的文件
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.72,0:19:22.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们已经在使用
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.07,0:19:25.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这样我们就可以很容易地使用相同的。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.87,0:19:30.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后在这里，让我们现在谈谈边界。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.20,0:19:31.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以边界，
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.70,0:19:35.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在在这个属性实际上是一个特殊的属性
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.44,0:19:38.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为它接受多个值。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.42,0:19:42.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以让我们将边框的宽度定义为五个像素，
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.97,0:19:45.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,边框的样式为实心，
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.77,0:19:51.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后边框的颜色为，
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.16,0:19:55.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们之前已经使用过的颜色，所以这个蓝色。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.01,0:19:56.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好的？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.28,0:19:57.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,让我们给它一个保险箱
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.53,0:19:59.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后我再解释一下
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.46,0:20:00.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为什么它会这样工作。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.95,0:20:05.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,事实上，这里都是蓝色边框。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.79,0:20:06.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,美丽的。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.25,0:20:11.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以回到这个边界属性，
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.12,0:20:13.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这实际上是一种特殊的属性。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.81,0:20:17.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以它被称为速记属性，因为
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.10,0:20:19.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们可以只使用一个属性
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.16,0:20:21.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,用于定义三个不同的属性。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.90,0:20:26.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以我们也可以单独设置边框宽度，
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.17,0:20:29.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,边框样式和边框颜色属性。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.72,0:20:32.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但通常我们一口气做完
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.41,0:20:34.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并简单地同时定义所有内容。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.04,0:20:39.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在在这里，您可以定义很多不同的关键字。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.36,0:20:43.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,例如，dotted 总是一种可能性。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.38,0:20:48.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以这看起来像这样。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.40,0:20:53.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,您也可以使用虚线，它看起来像这样。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.33,0:20:59.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但通常我从不使用这些。我总是追求固体。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.57,0:21:01.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好的。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.40,0:21:04.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以这给了我们整个边界
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.97,0:21:07.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,围绕整个元素。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.29,0:21:11.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是，我们只想要顶部和底部的边框。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.20,0:21:15.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以不是像这样定义边界属性，
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.76,0:21:19.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,此属性也有特殊的变体。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.31,0:21:22.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以我们也可以说边界顶部。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.35,0:21:24.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以，正如你所料，
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.70,0:21:29.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们只会在元素的顶部设置边框样式。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.02,0:21:30.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以就像这样。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.92,0:21:32.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好的？
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.92,0:21:36.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后让我们选择所有这些并粘贴到这里
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.36,0:21:39.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为我们还想要底部的边框。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.16,0:21:43.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如此简单的边框底部。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.46,0:21:45.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,给它一个保险箱，我们开始吧。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.81,0:21:49.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只是为了完整起见，
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.72,0:21:54.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们也可以说左边界和右边界。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.88,0:22:00.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后我们将回到第一方
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.31,0:22:03.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们在所有四个方面都有边界。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.25,0:22:05.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以当然，这没有意义
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.93,0:22:08.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那么我们将简单地使用边界属性。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.69,0:22:11.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些我们无论如何都不想要。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.82,0:22:15.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以我们回到了这个结果。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.62,0:22:16.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好的。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.45,0:22:20.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这就是我们在 CSS 中使用颜色的方式。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.33,0:22:23.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在让我快速提一下，我们也可以使用
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.24,0:22:26.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些预定义的颜色名称就像我们所做的一样
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.40,0:22:29.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一开始是蓝色的。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.81,0:22:33.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这么快就给你看。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.34,0:22:36.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,假设我们要设置背景颜色
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.55,0:22:38.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对于整个网页。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.43,0:22:42.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以这也可以通过添加样式来实现
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.25,0:22:43.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,到身体。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.98,0:22:49.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以我们可以像这样做背景颜色，
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.32,0:22:54.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这里我们可以指定这些名称之一。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.86,0:22:56.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以如果我给它一个保险箱，
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.72,0:23:01.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那么一切都有这种非常美丽的蓝色
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.12,0:23:02.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,作为背景。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.45,0:23:06.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当然除了我们特别给出的元素
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.44,0:23:08.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,另一种背景颜色。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.65,0:23:09.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对？
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.13,0:23:12.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或者我们可以使用其他东西。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.88,0:23:16.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以通常如果你刚开始写一些颜色名称，
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.61,0:23:20.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你会从 VS 代码中得到很多建议
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.37,0:23:22.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后你可以像这样选择其中一个。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.21,0:23:25.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好的？
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.04,0:23:26.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但我们当然不希望这样
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.34,0:23:29.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以让我们通过点击注释来注释掉这段代码
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.75,0:23:34.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或控制斜线，然后我们就恢复正常了。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.16,0:23:34.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好的。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.99,0:23:38.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在，只是为了巩固这些知识，
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.35,0:23:42.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我建议你尝试这三个属性
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.12,0:23:43.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们刚刚学到的。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.57,0:23:47.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,例如，通过为更多元素添加边框，
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.36,0:23:49.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,比如一些标题或一些列表，
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.81,0:23:52.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并且还更改了更多的文本颜色
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.41,0:23:56.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尤其重要的是玩
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.40,0:24:00.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,用你自己的颜色选择器一点点。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.35,0:24:03.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以只需花 10 或 15 分钟即可完成
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.03,0:24:05.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后我会在下一个视频中见到你。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.47,0:00:03.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome back.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.07,0:00:04.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In this lecture,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.01,0:00:08.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,we will learn how to work with colors in CSS.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.30,0:00:12.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However, before we can actually go back to our CSS,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.55,0:00:15.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,we first need to learn a little bit about the theory
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.75,0:00:18.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,of how to represent colors using code.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.97,0:00:24.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now, there are many ways of representing colors
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.02,0:00:28.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,in computers and basically in writing code,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.10,0:00:32.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but one of the more traditional models is the RGB model.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.83,0:00:34.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So in the RGB model,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.79,0:00:37.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,every single color can be represented
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.51,0:00:42.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,by any combination of red, green, and blue colors.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.03,0:00:45.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So that looks something like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.95,0:00:49.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And maybe you have already seen a diagram like this
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.06,0:00:51.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,somewhere in school or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.63,0:00:57.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So anyway, in order to actually represent a certain color,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.83,0:01:00.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,we need to give each of the three base colors,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.90,0:01:05.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,any value between zero and 255.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.16,0:01:06.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so with that,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.54,0:01:11.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,we can define a total of 16.8 million different colors.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.22,0:01:16.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So let's understand this a little bit using our diagram here
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.46,0:01:19.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and starting with the pure red color.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.35,0:01:24.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, in this channel, red is at the complete maximum,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.22,0:01:28.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,which is 255 and the other two channels.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.32,0:01:31.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So the other two base colors are at zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.97,0:01:36.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So there is no green whatsoever and no blue whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.71,0:01:39.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so this is why this is pure red.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.51,0:01:40.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So again,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.39,0:01:42.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,the red channel is at the maximum value
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.93,0:01:45.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and all the other ones are at zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.60,0:01:49.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And the same of course, for blue and for green.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.26,0:01:54.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So in blue, the blue channel is at a maximum of 255,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.10,0:01:57.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and the other one's at zero and in green,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.32,0:02:00.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,basically the same happens for green.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.29,0:02:02.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Next up we have white.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.60,0:02:05.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And in white, we have all the three colors
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.52,0:02:08.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,at the maximum of 255.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.83,0:02:12.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So basically having all the colors at maximum
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.39,0:02:15.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,gives us a complete white while at the other end
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.89,0:02:19.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,of the spectrum, when we have all the colors at zero,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.70,0:02:22.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,we get a complete black color.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.64,0:02:26.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Finally, the other three colors that we have here
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.20,0:02:30.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,are a mix of the other two colors that they are made of.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.33,0:02:34.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So you'll see that this magenta here is red and blue
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.04,0:02:37.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,at the maximum and no green at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.37,0:02:42.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then we have this I think is called cyan or cyan color,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.41,0:02:47.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,which has a red at zero and GNB at its maximum.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.40,0:02:50.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And finally yellow has blue at zero
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.45,0:02:53.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and the other two at 255.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.02,0:02:54.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Great.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.88,0:02:57.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So I hope that this makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.71,0:03:00.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And now that we have a basic understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.62,0:03:03.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,of how the RGB model works,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.04,0:03:06.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,let's actually see how we can represent
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.16,0:03:09.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,or how we can define colors in CSS.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.53,0:03:14.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So in CSS, we have two ways of writing colors
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.38,0:03:16.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,using the RGB model.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.30,0:03:21.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And those are the RGB notation and hexadecimal notation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.41,0:03:24.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So by using the RGB notation,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.22,0:03:28.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,all we do is to use this RGB function in CSS,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.49,0:03:31.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and then we simply specify the values for each
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.76,0:03:35.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,of the three color channels, red, green, and blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.66,0:03:37.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So for example,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.06,0:03:40.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,if we set green and blue to the maximum values,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.54,0:03:44.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,then we get this cyan color just as we saw
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.68,0:03:46.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,in the last slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.57,0:03:50.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Another example, which is a lot more real world,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.12,0:03:52.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,is this orange color right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.92,0:03:55.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So here are the numbers for each channel
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.08,0:03:57.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,look a little bit more random.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.47,0:04:00.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so this is how we get a real looking color
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.81,0:04:04.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,using CSS and using the RGB notation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.81,0:04:07.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then besides the normal RGB function,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.96,0:04:11.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,there is also RGB with transparency.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.82,0:04:14.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And transparency is also called alpha.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.89,0:04:18.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so that's why this function is called RGBA.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.66,0:04:22.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So here we can specify a fourth value,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.05,0:04:24.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,which in this case is the 0.3,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.05,0:04:28.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and this will then give this color a transparency
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.35,0:04:29.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,as we can see here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.75,0:04:34.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Looking at this other example, if we, for example define
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.93,0:04:36.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,an alpha value of 0.7,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.48,0:04:40.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,then we see that this color is actually transparent
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.93,0:04:44.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,as visible when we put it on top of another color
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.66,0:04:47.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,like this green square.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.12,0:04:50.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now, of course we don't have to manually come up
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.11,0:04:52.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,with these numbers for these colors.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.61,0:04:53.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.66,0:04:57.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So we don't have to like manually write 244, 179, 63
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.80,0:05:02.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,in order to get this orange.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.00,0:05:06.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So usually we just copy a certain color from somewhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.32,0:05:10.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,or we can also generate it with a color picker in VS code.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.96,0:05:14.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so that will then automatically give us these numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.51,0:05:17.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But all this is still very important so that you know
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.64,0:05:20.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,what these numbers actually mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.30,0:05:22.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. But moving on,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.17,0:05:25.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,let's now talk about the hexadecimal notation,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.48,0:05:29.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,which is actually a bit more used in CSS.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.03,0:05:31.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So here in the hexadecimal notation,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.80,0:05:36.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,we don't use a scale from zero to 255,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.25,0:05:40.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but instead we use a scale from zero to FF.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.76,0:05:45.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And FF is basically the same as 255,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.40,0:05:48.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but in a hexadecimal scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.20,0:05:51.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And we don't need to go into what that actually means,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.90,0:05:54.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but basically hexadecimal numbers
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.08,0:05:58.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,do not go from zero to nine, but from zero to 15.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.83,0:06:02.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So there are 16 different numbers and not just 10,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.54,0:06:05.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and the last one F.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.08,0:06:10.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so that's why FF here means 255.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.54,0:06:13.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now translating that to CSS,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.27,0:06:16.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,we write hexadecimal notation like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.26,0:06:20.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,with the hash then the value for red, green, and blue,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.73,0:06:23.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,just as I have it here on this screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.20,0:06:25.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so this then gives us, of course
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.28,0:06:29.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,the exact same number as with the RGB notation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.28,0:06:30.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And the same can of course be done
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.96,0:06:35.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,with this orange example color that I have down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.23,0:06:37.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So we can represent as using F4B33F.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.11,0:06:43.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And again, this looks kind of random
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.07,0:06:46.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and so we usually just copy us from the color picker
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.32,0:06:47.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,in VS code.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.94,0:06:50.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now in hexadecimal notation,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.03,0:06:52.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,there's also something called the shorthand,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.94,0:06:57.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,which we can use when all the colors are identical pairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.59,0:07:02.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So in our cyan color here, we have two zeros, two Fs,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.10,0:07:03.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and again, two Fs.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.69,0:07:07.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so we can abbreviate debt into our shorthand
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.08,0:07:07.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,writing 0FF.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.47,0:07:10.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.82,0:07:14.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And now a little bit about how we actually do things
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.01,0:07:17.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,in practice in the real world.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.07,0:07:21.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So in practice, we mostly use the hexadecimal notation,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.78,0:07:26.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and then if we need transparency, we use the RGBA function.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.19,0:07:30.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So as you see here on the left side with the alpha value.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.83,0:07:34.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Finally, just something about grace,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.59,0:07:36.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,which are a special kind of color
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.73,0:07:39.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,that we need all the time in CSS.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.49,0:07:42.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So basically in the RGB model,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.25,0:07:44.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,when the three colors in the three channels
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.93,0:07:49.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,are exactly the same, what we get is a gray color.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.51,0:07:52.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So at both extremes of the spectrum,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.78,0:07:56.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,when all of the values are zero, we get complete black,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.73,0:08:01.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and when all of them are at maximum, so at 205,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.79,0:08:05.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,or at FF then we get white.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.58,0:08:07.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But of course there are many other gray colors
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.94,0:08:10.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,in between that we can use.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.48,0:08:11.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And to be precise,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.63,0:08:16.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,there are exactly 256 pure grays to choose from.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.09,0:08:20.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And one of them is this one, for example.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.60,0:08:25.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So where red, green, and blue are all at 69.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.15,0:08:28.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So this gives us this nice gray color,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.18,0:08:33.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,which has the hexadecimal code of 444444
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.14,0:08:38.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,which in the shorthand notation can be written as just 444.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.73,0:08:42.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So this one, I like to use a lot for text color.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.33,0:08:45.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And of course, let's take a look at another example.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.24,0:08:49.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And this one that has all the values at 183,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.12,0:08:53.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and it can be represented as B7B7B7.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.35,0:08:55.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So in the hexadecimal notation
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.81,0:08:59.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,you will see once again that the three pairs here
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.31,0:09:01.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,are exactly the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.00,0:09:04.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so this is the signal dead we have in fact,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.26,0:09:05.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,a gray color.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.21,0:09:07.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.04,0:09:10.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So now that we know a little bit about the theory of color
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.05,0:09:13.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,in code and in CSS code in particular,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.94,0:09:17.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,let's now quickly learn a couple of CSS properties
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.28,0:09:20.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,where we can actually use colors in practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.81,0:09:26.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And the most simple CSS property that requires a color value
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.36,0:09:28.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,is simply the color property,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.56,0:09:30.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,which we actually already used before.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.94,0:09:36.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So let's say that we want this H1 here to have
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.17,0:09:37.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,a different color.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.00,0:09:41.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So let's say color,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.98,0:09:46.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and then I will just specify some blue color here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.22,0:09:48.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,1098 and ad.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.58,0:09:53.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so this gives us this nice blue color.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.32,0:09:55.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So as we just learned,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.81,0:10:00.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,we have 10 or one zero in the red channel,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.57,0:10:05.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,98 in the green channel and ad in the blue channel.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.97,0:10:08.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now, as I mentioned before,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.52,0:10:11.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,we usually use a the VS code color picker.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.66,0:10:14.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So we get that by simply hovering over a color,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.90,0:10:18.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and then from here, we can choose like any color
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.17,0:10:19.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,that we want.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.40,0:10:21.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.87,0:10:24.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So we can change the color here to something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.80,0:10:27.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So this shade of gray, and then in there,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.95,0:10:31.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,we can basically define how dark that gray should be.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.07,0:10:35.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Also if we click here at the top,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.15,0:10:38.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,so in this value here, that will change the notation.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.34,0:10:41.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So now we have this HSL,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.47,0:10:43.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,which we actually didn't talk about,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.74,0:10:47.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but then if we click again, we got the RGB.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.18,0:10:50.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so this is exactly the same color as before,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.40,0:10:52.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but using the RGB function.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.40,0:10:54.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.67,0:10:56.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So let me save it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.12,0:10:58.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And now you'll see that we have this green color.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.41,0:11:04.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So if we hover it again, we get back to the color picker.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.34,0:11:06.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And now this one here is actually the slider
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.68,0:11:08.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,for the alpha value.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.70,0:11:10.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So if we start dragging it down,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.78,0:11:15.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,then you see that automatically it gets changed to RGBA.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.70,0:11:16.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.53,0:11:20.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And then here we can, as I mentioned define the alpha value.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.48,0:11:23.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So it actually already got saved,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.84,0:11:27.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and you see that now the color is kind of transparent.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.43,0:11:29.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.29,0:11:33.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And if we put it even down close to zero,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.37,0:11:36.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,then now it's almost completely faded out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.72,0:11:40.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.05,0:11:43.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So this is how we work with the color picker,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.02,0:11:46.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but now let's actually go back to the color that we had.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.95,0:11:47.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So 1098ad.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.29,0:11:52.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.79,0:11:55.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Actually another nice trick that I wanted to show you,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.85,0:11:59.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,so if you just want the color picker,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.04,0:12:04.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,you can just specify any color first, for example, white,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.11,0:12:07.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,by using FFF, and then you just hovered the color
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.16,0:12:09.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and then you get to the color picker.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.73,0:12:12.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.56,0:12:15.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So if you want it, for example, this pink,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.43,0:12:19.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,you can choose that here, maybe with some alpha
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.76,0:12:21.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and there you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.23,0:12:24.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And now it applied this pink color,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.05,0:12:27.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,because when we have two same definitions,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.35,0:12:28.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,it will simply use the last one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.82,0:12:32.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But again, more about that a bit later.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.00,0:12:35.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So let's get rid of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.21,0:12:39.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And now we actually also want the h2 and the h3
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.28,0:12:40.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,with the exact same color.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.03,0:12:43.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So this one and this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.96,0:12:47.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So how should we do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.10,0:12:50.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Should we simply copied this property here
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.77,0:12:54.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,to this declaration and then paste it here and here?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.63,0:12:57.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, not really, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.59,0:13:00.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because then we would have the exact same code
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.11,0:13:01.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,in multiple places.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.61,0:13:05.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And that is never a good idea, because imagine that,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.00,0:13:09.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,then we wanted to change the color, for example to orange.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.03,0:13:10.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then we would have to go through
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.87,0:13:14.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,all the three color definitions and change them there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.90,0:13:16.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So change them one by one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.96,0:13:20.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And of course that's not what we want.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.07,0:13:24.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So instead, we can define a list of selectors,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.53,0:13:26.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,just like we did here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.54,0:13:29.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But now only with the ones that we want
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.60,0:13:31.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,the blue collar to apply to.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.09,0:13:35.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So that's h1, h2, h3
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.16,0:13:41.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and now let's simply grab that and paste it here,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.04,0:13:44.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,give it a safe and there you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.26,0:13:50.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So now the h1, h2, and h3 have this blue color.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.15,0:13:55.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And now, as you also might've noticed one more time,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.55,0:14:00.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,we have now yet another selector that is applying to the h1.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.79,0:14:04.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So we have this one and this one and this one,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.19,0:14:07.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and in fact, all the styles of all of them
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.75,0:14:10.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,are now applying to this element.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.45,0:14:15.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Next up, let's also define a color for the rest of the text.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.29,0:14:19.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So right now the rest of the text is completely black,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.15,0:14:22.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but let's use that gray color that I showed you
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.66,0:14:23.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,in one of the slides.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.81,0:14:27.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And actually let's do that here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.17,0:14:31.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So we want this text to apply to everything basically,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.90,0:14:36.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,even these here and the color will then get overwritten
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.67,0:14:38.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,later.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.26,0:14:40.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And again, we will learn about why
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.21,0:14:42.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and how that works in a separate lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.97,0:14:45.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So remember for a gray color,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.88,0:14:49.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,it needs to have the same values in all three channels.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.10,0:14:54.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so let's say 444444, like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.23,0:14:56.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and if you'll remember the shorthand,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.61,0:14:58.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,then we can abbreviate this even more.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.89,0:15:02.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because each of the pairs is the same value
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.21,0:15:04.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,as always just 44,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.51,0:15:07.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and so we can make this even shorter just like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.95,0:15:10.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Give it a safe,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.27,0:15:15.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and now indeed, all of this text here is a this gray color,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.72,0:15:18.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,except for the h1, two and three,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.11,0:15:20.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,which are overwritten here a little bit later.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.40,0:15:22.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Great.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.32,0:15:25.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So let's now talk about another CSS property
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.44,0:15:27.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,that can accept a color value,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.92,0:15:30.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and that is the background color property.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.72,0:15:33.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So let's now give our main page header
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.01,0:15:37.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,a slight gray background color to distinguish it a bit
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.13,0:15:39.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,from the rest of the content.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.45,0:15:42.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So how could we do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.83,0:15:45.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's come all the way down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.14,0:15:47.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And the first thing that comes to mind
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.16,0:15:52.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,is to simply select header like this, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.08,0:15:56.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so here is that new property called background color.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.05,0:16:03.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And here let's use another nice gray color,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.61,0:16:04.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,which is F7F7F7.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.68,0:16:11.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So again, you can see that the colors in the three colors,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.36,0:16:16.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,so the three main RGB channels are exactly the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.08,0:16:19.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And by the way, here in the color picker,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.14,0:16:23.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,no matter what color you're in here in this color slider
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.62,0:16:27.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,here on the left there is always this shade of grays.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.52,0:16:29.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So if you start here from the top,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.49,0:16:32.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,you see the white that I showed you in this slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.26,0:16:36.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And at the very top, you get then to black.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.09,0:16:36.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.95,0:16:39.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So you can always get a gray color
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.36,0:16:42.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,if you move the slider here at the very extreme
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.96,0:16:45.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,of this left side here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.35,0:16:48.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But now let's go to F7F7, which is a color,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.95,0:16:52.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,which is nice to memorize and nice to use.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.40,0:16:56.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So very subtle gray, maybe you cannot even see it here,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.83,0:16:59.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but hopefully you will see it on your screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.36,0:17:01.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now, the problem here is that not only,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.36,0:17:04.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,our page header got the gray color,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.07,0:17:05.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but also this other header.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.67,0:17:09.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So maybe you could see that coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.54,0:17:13.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so the solution to that is to give this header a name
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.80,0:17:16.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and then style only this header.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.51,0:17:19.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now there's only this one header that we want to style,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.90,0:17:22.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and so we could use an ID here,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.69,0:17:25.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but given what I explained in the last lecture,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.31,0:17:28.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,let's not do that, and that's simply use a class.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.76,0:17:32.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's call it main header.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.86,0:17:35.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let me copy it
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.49,0:17:42.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and replace this header with the main header class.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.06,0:17:46.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And indeed now only this one here got this gray color.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.67,0:17:48.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's just get rid of this test.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.23,0:17:51.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.58,0:17:53.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.41,0:17:55.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And if you can't really see this background color,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.35,0:17:58.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,then just use your color picker
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.27,0:18:01.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,to just use some other shade of gray.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.32,0:18:02.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.27,0:18:05.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And this video is already running quite long,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.30,0:18:08.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but let's still talk about another property here,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.61,0:18:10.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,which is about borders.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.89,0:18:15.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So what I want to do next is to add some border
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.01,0:18:18.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,to these related posts here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.37,0:18:22.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So basically to make them now look something like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.55,0:18:24.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.38,0:18:27.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So we have at the bottom and at the top here,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.26,0:18:28.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,this blue border.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.65,0:18:32.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So that's not hard to do at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.37,0:18:34.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So let's just see what's the element here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.94,0:18:37.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And it is this slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.35,0:18:40.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So let's just select it here
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.64,0:18:45.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,using this element selector.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.94,0:18:50.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So element selector is basically when we simply use the name
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.25,0:18:52.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,of the element to select it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.64,0:18:53.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.48,0:18:56.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So this year is the class selector with a dot.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.39,0:18:58.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is the ID selector with the hash.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.92,0:19:01.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And when we simply use the name of the element,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.33,0:19:04.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,we call that the element selector.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.17,0:19:06.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now let's start by actually giving it the same
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.93,0:19:08.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,background color.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.51,0:19:11.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So background color
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.17,0:19:14.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and then we use the one that we used before.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.27,0:19:16.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And VS code is actually very helpful here
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.72,0:19:20.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,because it scans the CSS document for the files
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.72,0:19:22.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,that we're already using
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.07,0:19:25.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,so that we can very easily use the same ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.87,0:19:30.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And then here, let's now talk about the border.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.20,0:19:31.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So border,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.70,0:19:35.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and now at this property is actually a special property
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.44,0:19:38.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,because it accepts multiple values.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.42,0:19:42.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So let's define the width of the border as five pixels,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.97,0:19:45.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,the style of the border as solid,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.77,0:19:51.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and then the color of the border as,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.16,0:19:55.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,that color that we already use before, so this blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.01,0:19:56.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.28,0:19:57.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's just give it a safe
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.53,0:19:59.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and then I will explain a little bit more
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.46,0:20:00.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,why it works this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.95,0:20:05.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And indeed here is all blue border.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.79,0:20:06.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.25,0:20:11.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So going back here to this border property,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.12,0:20:13.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,this is actually a special kind of property.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.81,0:20:17.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So it's called a shorthand property because
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.10,0:20:19.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,we can just use one property
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.16,0:20:21.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,for defining three different properties.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.90,0:20:26.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So we could also individually style the border width,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.17,0:20:29.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,border style and border color properties.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.72,0:20:32.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But usually we do it all in one run
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.41,0:20:34.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and simply define everything at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.04,0:20:39.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now here, you can define a lot of different keywords.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.36,0:20:43.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For example, dotted is always a possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.38,0:20:48.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So this will look something like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.40,0:20:53.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You can use dashed as well, which will look like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.33,0:20:59.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But usually I never used those. I always go for solid.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.57,0:21:01.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.40,0:21:04.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So this it gives us the entire border
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.97,0:21:07.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,around the entire element.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.29,0:21:11.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However, we only want the border at the top and the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.20,0:21:15.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so instead of defining the border property like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.76,0:21:19.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,there are also special variants of this property.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.31,0:21:22.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So we can also say border top.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.35,0:21:24.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so this, as you might expect,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.70,0:21:29.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,we'll only style the border at the top side of the element.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.02,0:21:30.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So just like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.92,0:21:32.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.92,0:21:36.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's select all of this and paste it here
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.36,0:21:39.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,because we also want the border at the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.16,0:21:43.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So easy enough border bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.46,0:21:45.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Give it a safe, and here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.81,0:21:49.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And just for the sake of completeness,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.72,0:21:54.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,we can also say border left and border right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.88,0:22:00.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so then we will be back to square one
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.31,0:22:03.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,where we have the borders on all the four sides.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.25,0:22:05.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so of course, this doesn't make sense
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.93,0:22:08.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,then we would simply use the border property.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.69,0:22:11.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,These ones we don't want anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.82,0:22:15.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so we are back to this result.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.62,0:22:16.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.45,0:22:20.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And this is how we work with colors in CSS.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.33,0:22:23.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now let me just quickly mention that we can also use
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.24,0:22:26.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,these predefined color names just as we did
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.40,0:22:29.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,in the very beginning with the color of blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.81,0:22:33.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So quickly show that to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.34,0:22:36.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So let's say that we wanted to set a background color
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.55,0:22:38.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,for the entire webpage.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.43,0:22:42.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So that's also possible simply by adding a style
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.25,0:22:43.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,to the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.98,0:22:49.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So we can just do background color like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.32,0:22:54.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and here we can specify one of these names.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.86,0:22:56.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So if I give it a safe,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.72,0:23:01.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,then everything has this very beautiful blue color
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.12,0:23:02.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,as the background.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.45,0:23:06.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Except of course the elements that we specifically gave
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.44,0:23:08.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,another background color.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.65,0:23:09.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.13,0:23:12.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Or we could use something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.88,0:23:16.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So usually if you just start writing some color name,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.61,0:23:20.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,you will get a lot of suggestions here from VS code
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.37,0:23:22.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and then you can select one of them like this.
